Any question about administration?

What software do we need?

  • R is a programming language for statistical computing
    • R Studio is an integrated development environment (IDE) for R programming
    • R Markdown is a markup language for combining R code with text
  • Python is widely used for data science and machine learning
    • Anaconda is an integrated development environment (IDE) for Python programming
    • Jupyter is a markup language for combining Python code with text

All of these are free

Installing R

  • R can be downloaded from the ``Comprehensive R Archive Network" (CRAN).
  • R can be installed on Windows, Mac or Linux operating systems.
  • In this course, the instructors will run R on Mac.
  • To install R, visit the R website, http://www.r-project.org and follow the installation directions (see the FAQ section for more details).
  • R version 4.0 and above are required for this class.

R Console

  • open R console

RStudio

  • RStudio is a free and open source integrated development environment (IDE) designed specifically for R. http://www.rstudio.com
  • Runs on, Windows, Mac or Linux operating systems.
  • Useful productivity tools
    • Syntax highlighting, smart indention, parentheses matching
    • Easily execute code from the source editor
    • Integrates all of the tools (source editor, console, plots, documentation, and more) when working with R into a single environment
    • Extensive tools for developing R packages
    • Interactive debugging for diagnosing and fixing errors

R markdown

  • Will be introduced today if there are any remaining time
  • Otherwise will be introduced next Monday

Install Python

  • Python can be installed on Windows, Mac or Linux operating systems.
  • In this course, the instructors will run Python on Mac.
  • To install Python, visit the Python website, https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-3106/.
  • Python version 3.8 and above are required for this class.

Python Console

  • open Python console via command line:
    • MAC user:
      • Open Terminal
      • just typing python, python3, python3.8, or python3.9
    • Windows user:
      • open the Start Menu via clicking the Start Button
      • Click Windows System, then select Command Prompt with the black icon.
      • just typing python, python3, python3.8, or python3.9

Anaconda

  • Anaconda is a free and open source integrated development environment (IDE) for python. https://www.anaconda.com
  • Runs on, Windows, Mac or Linux operating systems.
  • Useful productivity tools
    • Integrate many popular data science tools including Jupyter, PyCharm
    • Allow creating user level environment independent of the operating system or admin libraries

Comparison of R and Python

  • Commonality:
    • both are open source languages, free to use for everyone
    • both are well suited for data science
      • data clearning
      • data manipulation
      • data visualization
  • Difference:
    • R is rooted in statistical analysis.
    • Python is general-purpose programming language, more widely used in machine learning and deep learning

Some drawbacks of R and Python

  • R and Python are slow in loop (e.g.for, while), so try to avoid loops if you run a large program and care about speed.
    • Solution: vectorize your program.

Things you should have done, by the end of this week

  • Install R (>4.0) and R Studio on your laptop
  • Install Python (>3.8) and Anaconda on your laptop
